============================================================
8. Parent POM - Ban Old javax and Legacy UI Dependencies
============================================================

Add Maven Enforcer plugin to parent pom.xml:

<build>
    <plugins>
        <plugin>
            <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
            <artifactId>maven-enforcer-plugin</artifactId>
            <executions>
                <execution>
                    <id>ban-javax-and-legacy-ui</id>
                    <goals>
                        <goal>enforce</goal>
                    </goals>
                    <configuration>
                        <rules>
                            <requireJavaVersion>
                                <version>[21,22)</version>
                            </requireJavaVersion>

                            <requireMavenVersion>
                                <version>[3.9.0,)</version>
                            </requireMavenVersion>

                            <dependencyConvergence />

                            <requireUpperBoundDeps />

                            <bannedDependencies>
                                <excludes>
                                    <exclude>javax.servlet:*</exclude>
                                    <exclude>javax.servlet.jsp:*</exclude>
                                    <exclude>javax.el:*</exclude>
                                    <exclude>javax.faces:*</exclude>
                                    <exclude>javax.ws.rs:*</exclude>
                                    <exclude>javax.xml.bind:*</exclude>
                                    <exclude>javax.xml.ws:*</exclude>
                                    <exclude>javax.jws:*</exclude>
                                    <exclude>javax.annotation:*</exclude>
                                    <exclude>javax.validation:*</exclude>
                                    <exclude>javax.activation:*</exclude>

                                    <exclude>com.sun.jersey:*</exclude>
                                    <exclude>org.richfaces:*</exclude>
                                    <exclude>org.jboss.richfaces:*</exclude>
                                </excludes>
                            </bannedDependencies>
                        </rules>
                    </configuration>
                </execution>
            </executions>
        </plugin>
    </plugins>
</build>

Purpose:

- Stop old Java EE / javax dependencies entering through transitive dependencies.
- Stop RichFaces / JSF leakage into core modules.
- Stop Spring/Jersey/JAXB conflicts early.

