============================================================
20. Build Order
============================================================

Use this exact order.

Step 1: Parent validation

mvn -N validate

Step 2: Schema only

mvn -pl schema clean install -DskipTests

Fix all JAXB/WSDL generation issues here first.

Step 3: Config with dependencies

mvn -pl config -am clean install -DskipTests

Step 4: Application compile

mvn -pl application -am clean compile -DskipTests

Step 5: Application tests

mvn -pl application -am test

Step 6: Full core build

mvn clean verify

Because parent has only 3 modules now, this builds only:

schema
config
application

============================================================
21. Dependency Validation Commands
============================================================

Run all of these.

Check for old javax:

mvn dependency:tree -Dincludes=javax.*

Expected:

Ideally empty.

Check JAXB:

mvn dependency:tree -Dincludes=javax.xml.bind,jakarta.xml.bind,com.sun.xml.bind,org.glassfish.jaxb

Expected:

jakarta.xml.bind-api
org.glassfish.jaxb:jaxb-runtime

Not expected:

javax.xml.bind:jaxb-api
com.sun.xml.bind:jaxb-impl

Check JAX-WS:

mvn dependency:tree -Dincludes=javax.xml.ws,jakarta.xml.ws,com.sun.xml.ws

Expected:

com.sun.xml.ws:rt
jakarta.xml.ws-api

Not expected:

javax.xml.ws:jaxws-api

Check Jersey:

mvn dependency:tree -Dincludes=org.glassfish.jersey,com.sun.jersey,javax.ws.rs,jakarta.ws.rs

Expected:

org.glassfish.jersey 3.1.x
jakarta.ws.rs-api

Not expected:

com.sun.jersey
javax.ws.rs-api

Check Spring:

mvn dependency:tree -Dincludes=org.springframework

Expected:

Only Spring 6.2.x.

Not expected:

Spring 4.x
Spring 5.x
mixed Spring versions

Check RichFaces/JSF leakage:

mvn dependency:tree -Dincludes=org.richfaces,org.jboss.richfaces,javax.faces,jakarta.faces

Expected for this phase:

nothing

Because webapp is not part of this migration yet.

============================================================
22. Final Migration Checklist
============================================================

1. Remove webapp from parent module build.
2. Set Java 21 and Maven 3.9.
3. Upgrade Spring 4.x to Spring 6.2.x.
4. Upgrade Jersey to Jersey 3.1.x.
5. Replace JAXB with Jakarta JAXB 4.
6. Replace JAX-WS with Metro/JAX-WS 4.
7. Regenerate XSD/WSDL classes.
8. Change javax.xml.bind to jakarta.xml.bind.
9. Change javax.xml.ws to jakarta.xml.ws.
10. Change javax.jws to jakarta.jws.
11. Change javax.ws.rs to jakarta.ws.rs.
12. Change javax.annotation to jakarta.annotation.
13. Change javax.validation to jakarta.validation.
14. Remove RichFaces/JSF imports from application.
15. Add Maven Enforcer to block old javax dependencies.
16. Add exclusions for old transitive dependencies.
17. Build schema first.
18. Build config second.
19. Build application third.
20. Run dependency tree checks.

============================================================
23. Final Architecture Decision
============================================================

For this phase:

schema/config/application = full Jakarta now
webapp/RichFaces/JSF = separate later migration

Do not solve application build errors by adding:

- javax.faces
- jakarta.faces
- RichFaces
- old servlet jars

That will break the clean migration path to Tomcat 10 later.